  "prompt": "What are the components of a network interface card?",
  "response": "A Network Interface Card (NIC) consists of several key components:\n\n1. Physical Components:\n- Circuit board\n- Copper or fiber optic connector\n- MAC address ROM\n- Transceiver\n- Bus interface\n\n2. Electronic Components:\n- Network controller chip\n- Memory buffer\n- Oscillator/clock generator\n- Voltage regulators\n\n3. Functional Components:\n- Media Access Control (MAC) layer\n- Physical layer (PHY) interface\n- Data encoding/decoding circuitry\n- Packet filtering mechanism\n- Interrupt handling logic\n\n4. Connectivity Elements:\n- RJ-45 port (Ethernet)\n- Fiber optic port\n- Coaxial connector\n- Wireless antenna (for Wi-Fi NICs)\n\n5. Software Components:\n- Device driver\n- Firmware\n- Protocol support stack\n\n6. Additional Features:\n- LED indicators\n- Jumper switches\n- Wake-on-LAN capability\n- Hardware-based encryption\n\nThese components work together to enable network communication, convert data between digital and electrical/optical signals, and manage network transmission and reception processes.",
